ally in [[Chicago]] and [[Washington, D.C.]] Most deaths occurred in rural areas during events like the [[Elaine race riot]] in [[Arkansas]], where an estimated 100 to 240 blacks and 5 whites were killed. Other major events of Red Summer were the [[Chicago race riot of 1919|Chicago race riot]] and [[Washington race riot of 1919|Washington D.C. Race Riot]], which caused 38 and 39 deaths, respectively. Both riots had many more non-fatal injuries and extensive property damage reaching up into the millions of dollars.{{sfn|The New York Times|1919|p=}}\n\n==See also==\n{{Commons category}}\n*[[Washington race riot of 1919]]\n*[[Mass racial violence in the United States]]\n*[[List of incidents of civil unrest in the United States]]\n\n==Bibliography==\n'''Notes'''\n{{reflist|20em}}\n'''References'''\n{{refbegin|2}}\n*{{cite news |ref=harv|date= July 31, 1919|title= Newberry Negro Sought by Crowd|last=The Bamberg Herald|url=https://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn86063790/1919-07-31/ed-1/seq-1/#|newspaper=The Bamberg Herald|publisher=Henry S. Hartzog|location=[[Bamberg, South Carolina]]|issn=2379-4984|oclc=13608693 |pages=1-8|accessdate= July 21, 2019 }}\n*{{cite news |ref=harv|date= May 10, 1919|title= Soldier in Uniform is Beaten in Georgia Town|last=The Chicago Defender|authorlink=The Chicago Defender| newspaper=[[The Chicago Defender]]| location=Chicago|issn=0745-7014}}\n*{{cite web |ref=harv|last=Clark|first=James |date=December 9, 2016|url = https://taskandpurpose.com/tragic-ignored-history-black-veterans|title =The Tragic And Ignored History Of Black Veterans|publisher = [[Task & Purpose]]| accessdate = September 10, 2019 }}\n*{{cite web |ref=harv|last=Encyclopedia of Arkansas|authorlink=Encyclopedia of Arkansas History & Culture|date=2019|url = https://encyclopediaofarkansas.net/entries/clinton-briggs-8254/ |title =Clinton Briggs (Lynching of)|publisher = [[Encyclopedia of Arkansas History & Culture]]| accessdate = September 10, 2019 }}\n*{{cite web |ref=harv|las