rald and News|authorlink=Herald and News|url=https://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn86063758/1919-07-29/ed-1/seq-1/#|newspaper=[[Herald and News|The Herald and News]]|publisher=E.H. Aull|location=[[Newberry, South Carolina]]|issn=2333-2786|oclc=13640295|pages=1-8|accessdate= July 21, 2019 }}\n*{{cite book |ref=harv|last=James|first=Rawn , Jr.| authorlink = | title = The Double V: How Wars, Protest, and Harry Truman Desegregated America\u2019s Military|year=2013| publisher = Bloomsbury Publishing USA| isbn= 978-1-60819-617-3 }} <small>- Total pages: 336 </small>\n*{{cite news |ref=harv|date= December 29, 1919|title= Will offer $400 each for lynchers of Negro|last=The News Scimitar |url=https://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn98069867/1919-12-29/ed-1/seq-1/#|newspaper=The News Scimitar|publisher=Gilbert D. Raine|location=Memphis, Tennessee|issn= 2473-3199|oclc=39898320 |pages=1\u201316|accessdate= September 10, 2019 }}\n*{{cite news |ref=harv|title= For Action on Race Riot Peril| last=The New York Times|authorlink=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1919/10/05/archives/for-action-on-race-riot-peril-radical-propaganda-among-negroes.html|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|publisher=[[Adolph Ochs]]|location=New York, NY|issn=1553-8095|oclc=1645522|date=October 5, 1919|accessdate= July 5, 2019}}\n*{{cite book |ref=harv|last=Whitaker|first=Robert | authorlink = Robert Whitaker (author)| title = On the Laps of Gods: The Red Summer of 1919 and the Struggle for Justice That Remade a Nation|year=2009| publisher = [[Three Rivers Press]]| isbn=978-0-307-33983-6}} <small>- Total pages: 386 </small>\n*{{cite web |ref=harv|last=Stevenson |first=Bryan |authorlink=Bryan Stevenson |date=November 10, 2017|url = http://www.milwaukeeindependent.com/featured/bryan-stevenson-unspoken-history-lynching-african-american-veterans/|title =Bryan Stevenson: An Unspoken History of Lynching African-American Veterans |publisher = Milwaukee Independent | accessdate = September 10, 2019